m in V8 sporulation medium for conidia production"}},{"id":1054724,"guid":"425A181420744033A1E722E86603D209","order_id":1,"type_id":1,"title":"description","source":{"description":"<div class = \"text-blocks\"><div class = \"text-block\">Ground mycelium using a mortar and pistile in a laminal flow cabinet<\/div><div class = \"text-block\"><ul style = \"list-style-type:disc;\"><li style = \"counter-reset:ol0;list-style-type:disc;\"><span>cut 1 cm<\/span><span style = \"vertical-align:super;\">2<\/span><span> of mycelium and put it into a mortar<\/span><\/li><li style = \"counter-reset:ol0;list-style-type:disc;\">add 2.5 mL of destilled sterile water<\/li><li style = \"counter-reset:ol0;list-style-type:disc;\">grind to a non-pasty liquid consistency<\/li><li style = \"counter-reset:ol0;list-style-type:disc;\">pour 2.5 mL of the grind to each Petri dish containing V8 sporulation medium<\/li><li style = \"counter-reset:ol0;list-style-type:disc;\">the ground mycelium is distributed making circles, until the entire Petri dish is full of suspension<\/li><li style = \"counter-reset:ol0;list-style-type:disc;\">let the Petri dish for 20 min to dry, then seal with kleen pack<\/li><\/ul><\/div><\/div>"}}],"cases":null,"data":null,"section":null,"section_color":null},{"id":655420,"guid":"C2C2AD6EC9BE4B1A9DEBD8A2DA2B8745","previous_id":654491,"previous_guid":"E753BA089B584481A7588F0DDF2DD06C","modified_on":0,"protocol_id":0,"components":[{"id":1054723,"guid":"55C3955492324CF1AEAAF6DDD7536FB9","order_id":1,"type_id":6,"title":"Section","source":{"title":"Inoculation of ground mycelium in V8 sporulation medium for conidia production"}},{"id":1054724,"guid":"5369E53E17824815BF6919879328308E","order_id":1,"type_id":1,"title":"description","source":{"description":"<div class = \"text-blocks\"><div class = \"text-block\">The Petri dishes were put in the folowing culture condition for sporulation<\/div><div class = \"text-block\"><ul style = \"list-style-type:disc;\"><li style = \"counter-reset:ol0;list-style-type:disc;\">Room temperature 20 \u00b0C\u00a0<\/li><li style = \"counter-reset:ol0;list-style-type:disc;\">Continuous light with\u00a0cool-white fluorescent and black light (General Electric 15W\/18) emitting radiant energy in the near-ultraviolet or black light spectral range<\/li><li style = \"counter-reset:ol0;list-style-type:disc;\">Time in this conditions: for the firs harvest 5 days for the second harvest 3 days (same batch of petri dishes).  \n <\/li><\/ul><\/div><\/div>"}}],"cases":null,"data":null,"section":null,"section_color":null},{"id":655421,"guid":"78DB14B649F8431B8C57A39AA4797A24","previous_id":655420,"previous_guid":"C2C2AD6EC9BE4B1A9DEBD8A2DA2B8745","modified_on":0,"protocol_id":0,"components":[{"id":1054723,"guid":"909AC6F8673B428BAB9AEF40684E8FE4","order_id":1,"type_id":6,"title":"Section","source":{"title":"Harvest of conidia"}},{"id":1054724,"guid":"00B242D8817B40C49DACE2DD7FC23327","order_id":1,"type_id":1,"title":"description","source":{"description":"<div class = \"text-blocks\"><div class = \"text-block\">Harvest of conidia\u00a0 in a\u00a0laminal flow cabinet<\/div><div class = \"text-block\"><ol style = \"list-style-type: decimal;\"><li style = \"counter-reset:ol0;\">Take 2400 \u03bcL of grenetine (1%) and add it to the mycelium grown in the V8S medium<\/li><li style = \"counter-reset:ol0;\">Sweep gently with the camel bruch\u00a0<\/li><li style = \"counter-reset:ol0;\">Tilt the petri dish and with the help of the micropipette wash the mycelium with the same suspension<\/li><li style = \"counter-reset:ol0;\">\u00a0After harvesting put all the suspension in a Falcon 50 mL tube, the resulting suspension must be cloudy<\/li><\/ol><\/div><\/div>"}}],"cases":null,"data":null,"section":null,"section_color":null},{"id":657247,"guid":"65E55B97CDA44EC7BB040B7B8E11A213","previous_id":655421,"previous_guid":"78DB14B649F8431B8C57A39AA4797A24","modified_on":0,"protocol_id":0,"components":[{"id":1054723,"guid":"672F2B7114434601A3F733D1DA53EA45","order_id":1,"type_id":6,"title":"Section","source":{"title":" Conidia count"}},{"id":1054724,"guid":"A6F0738139E24254A79D429C22EA38A2","order_id":1,"type_id":1,"title":"description","source":{"description":"<div class = \"text-blocks\"><div class = \"text-block\">After the harvest take a sample for counting,\u00a0 if necessary you can dilute the suspension 1:10<\/div><div class = \"text-block\"><ol style = \"list-style-type: decimal;\"><li style = \"counter-reset:ol0;\">Use the\u00a0 Sedgwick-Rafter chamber to count the conidia (it could be the Neubauer chamber) using a\u00a0<\/li><li style = \"counter-reset:ol0;\">The following formula is used to calculate the concentration of conidia<\/li><\/ol><\/div><div class = \"text-block\"><span>cells or spores\/mL= \u03a3<\/span><span style = \":UNDERLINE;\">N x 1000 mm<\/span><span style = \":UNDERLINE;vertical-align:super;\">3<\/span><span>\u00a0 x dilution factor<\/span><\/div><div class = \"text-block\">\u00a0\u00a0\u00a0\u00a0\u00a0\u00a0\u00a0\u00a0\u00a0\u00a0\u00a0\u00a0\u00a0\u00a0\u00a0\u00a0\u00a0\u00a0\u00a0\u00a0\u00a0\u00a0\u00a0\u00a0\u00a0\u00a0\u00a0\u00a0\u00a0\u00a0\u00a0\u00a0\u00a0 A x D x F<\/div><div class = \"text-block\">Were:<\/div><div class = \"text-block\">N=Conidia counted<\/div><div class = \"text-block\"><span>A= field area 1 (mm<\/span><span style = \"vertical-align:super;\">2<\/span><span style = \"vertical-align:super;\">)<\/span><\/div><div class = \"text-block\">D= depth of field (1 mm)<\/div><div class = \"text-block\">F= numbers of counted fields (25)<\/div><div class = \"text-block\">\u00a0 \u00a0 \u00a0 \u00a0 \u00a0 \u00a0 \u00a0 \u00a0 \u00a03. Once the concentration of conidia is calculated, then the concentration of the original suspension is adjusted to 200 conidia per uL<\/div><div class = \"text-block\">\u00a0 \u00a0 \u00a0 \u00a0 \u00a0 \u00a0 \u00a0 \u00a0 \u00a04. If the conidia are not going to be used immediately, they can be stored at 4 \u00b0 C<\/div><\/div>"}}],"cases":null,"data":null,"section":null,"section_color":null}],"materials":[{"id":127803,"mol_weight":100.1,"name":"Calcium carbonate","linfor":null,"url":"https:\/\/www.sigmaaldrich.com\/mexico.html","sku":"C-5929","public":0,"vendor":{"name":"Sigma \u2013 Aldrich","affiliation":null,"username":null,"link":"https:\/\/www.sigmaaldrich.com\/","image":{"source":"https:\/\/www.protocols.io\/img\/vendors\/placeholder.png","placeholder":"https:\/\/www.protocols.io\/img\/vendors\/placeholder.png"},"badges":[],"research_interests":null,"id":298},"can_edit":0,"stats":{"total_protocols":0}},{"id":127804,"mol_weight":0,"name":"Agar-agar","linfor":null,"url":"https:\/\/www.sigmaaldrich.com\/mexico.html","sku":"1.01614.1000","public":0,"vendor":{"name":"Contributed by users","affiliation":null,"username":null,"link":"https:\/\/www.protocols.io","image":{"source":"https:\/\/www.protocols.io\/img\/vendors\/1.png","placeholder":"https:\/\/www.protocols.io\/img\/vendors\/1.png"},"badges":[],"research_interests":null,"id":1},"can_edit":0,"stats":{"total_protocols":0}}],"description":"<div class = \"text-blocks\"><div class = \"text-block\"><span>Continuous <\/span><span style = \"font-style:italic;\">in vitro<\/span><span> conidial production from <\/span><span style = \"font-style:italic;\">Mycosphaerella fijiensis<\/span><span> mycelium. A method for <\/span><span style = \"font-style:italic;\">in vitro<\/span><span> production of conidia is described. <\/span><span style = \"font-style:italic;\">M fijiensis<\/span><span> was grown on culture medium containing V8 juice. Mycelium was macerated until a fine suspension was produced; 2 mL was carefully spread on V8 sporulation medium. The Petri dishes were incubated for 6 days at 20 \u00b0C, under continuous cool-white fluorescent and black light. After the incubation period, 2.4 mL of 1% gelatin was added to each Petri dish, the conidia carefully dislodged with a camel hair brush. Conidial production was notably stimulated by brush harvesting mycelial cultures. After 6 days of culture the first harvest was made and the same batch of petri dishes were put in the same culture conditions to stimulate new conidial production. Significant cumulative conidial production was observed after the second harvest.<\/span><\/div><\/div>","changed_on":1553789164}